--> They have been distinguished from [[secondary sources]], which often cite, comment on, or build upon primary sources.<ref>Handlin (1954) 118-246</ref> They serve as an original source of [[information]] or new ideas about the topic. ''Primary'' and ''secondary'', however, are relative terms, and any given source may be classified as primary or secondary, depending on how it is used.<!--

